cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "grAIph: Topological Context Compilation for LLM Code Generation"
abstract: >
  grAIph implements Topological Context Compilation (TCC) — a novel architecture
  applying compiler theory to LLM context window management. The dependency graph
  is the source language. Kahn's algorithm determines generation order. An exponential
  decay formula governs context allocation. A multi-agent quality pipeline converts
  stochastic LLM output into verifiable, compilable code.
